The series' soundtrack is composed by [[Yoko Kanno]]. The opening theme song is "Trigger", composed by Kanno and performed by former [[Galileo Galilei (band)|Galileo Galilei]] vocalist [[Yuuki Ozaki]]. The ending theme song is {{nihongo4|"Dare ka, Umi o."|誰か、海を。||"Somebody, the Ocean."}}, composed by Kanno and performed by [[Aimer]].<ref name="cast" /> "Terror in Resonance Original Soundtrack 2 -crystalized-" was released on October 22, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=''_サウンドトラック第２弾発売決定！''|url=http://terror-in-tokyo.com/news_detail.html?id=31501|accessdate=August 29, 2014}}</ref> Artwork design by Ingibjörg Birgisdóttir.

Director Shinichirō Watanabe stated in interview with Otaku USA Magazine that the music of [[Iceland]]ic band [[Sigur Rós]] was the inspiration for the show and its soundtrack. {{quote|When I was listening to Sigur Rós, I got the visual image of two boys standing in the ruins of a destroyed city and that led to the idea of Terror In Resonance. ... we actually went to Iceland to record our music ...|Shinichirō Watanabe<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.otakuusamagazine.com/Anime/News1/Cowboy-Bebops-Shinichiro-Watanabe-and-Dai-Sato-Tal-8182.aspx|website=otakuusamagazine.com|author=Connor Foley|date=August 9, 2016|title=Cowboy Bebop's Shinichiro Watanabe and Dai Sato Talk Genre, Storytelling and Sigur Rós|accessdate=April 18, 2017}}</ref>}}

